article.headline: Cleveland St. 113, Wilberforce 61
article.story: CLEVELAND -- Jared Cunningham scored 18 points and Norris Cole 16 as Cleveland State ended a five-game losing streak with a 113-61 victory over NAIA opponent Wilberforce on Saturday. The Vikings (4-6) dominated throughout, finishing the first half with a 20-5 run in the final 5:20 to take a 52-26 lead. They shot 66.7 percent (24-for-36) in the second half to continue to pull away. Nigel Ajere scored 14 points, Jeremy Montgomery 12, D'Aundray Brown 11 and Trevon Harmon 10 as six Cleveland State players scored in double figures and all 12 Vikings scored. Cleveland State had a 40-18 advantage in rebounds and forced 25 turnovers by Wilberforce while committing 13. TyJaun Wallace scored 18 points and Taverius Wilkins 11 to lead Wilberforce.
